      "text": "Francisco public TV station."
    },
    {
      "line": 51,
      "text": "Jim Ludtke, air-brush artist,"
    },
    {
      "line": 52,
      "text": "freelances in New York."
    },
    {
      "line": 53,
      "text": "-Kevin Kelly"
    },
    {
      "line": 56,
      "text": "YSTICAL E-NGINE?"
    },
    {
      "line": 59,
      "text": "O THOSE WHO DON’T LIKE COMPUTERS, these ma-"
    },
    {
      "line": 60,
      "text": "chines seem to be a kind of monkey trap - a bottle with"
    },
    {
      "line": 61,
      "text": "fruit in it. The monkey reaches in and grasps the fruit, but"
    },
    {
      "line": 63,
      "text": "_ with the fruit in his fist he cannot get his hand out."
    },
    {
      "line": 65,
      "text": "The hone catches him because the monkey is unwilling to let go of"
    },
    {
      "line": 67,
      "text": "the fruit."
    },
    {
      "line": 70,
      "text": "It is not our hand that we put into the computer, it is our attention."
    },
    {
      "line": 71,
      "text": "Anyone who has watched the back of a mate or child bent before a"
    },
    {
      "line": 72,
      "text": "computer for hours can tell you: These machines hold attention like"
    },
    {
      "line": 73,
      "text": "no prior machine."
    },
    {
      "line": 76,
      "text": "To those of us who love these machines, they are a portal into"
    },
    {
      "line": 77,
      "text": "another, fascinating universe. It is a puzzle-world, full of possibilities."
    },
    {
      "line": 78,
      "text": "The beautiful patterns on the screen are just the two-dimensional"
    }
